<h1 id="ngx-restangular">Ngx-restangular</h1>
<p>This project is the follow-up of the <a href="https://github.com/mgonto/restangular/">Restangular</a>. Ngx-restangular is an Angular 2+ service that simplifies common GET, POST, DELETE, and UPDATE requests with a minimum of client code.
It's a perfect fit for any WebApp that consumes data from a RESTful API.</p>
<h1 id="demo">Demo</h1>
<p>Live Demo on Plunkr <a href="http://embed.plnkr.co/qozGPV2HowzmtKbC9a54/">Hero App</a>.
You can also check post about using ngx-restangular with <a href="https://restdb.io/">restdb.io</a> service in <a href="http://blog.2muchcoffee.com/angular_todo_application_with_ng2-restangular_and_restdb-io/">simple TODO Application</a></p>
<h1 id="current-stage">Current stage</h1>
<p>Ngx-restangular almost all functionality was transferred from the Restangular.
We are open to any cooperation in terms of its further development.</p>
<h1 id="renaming-from-ng2-restangular-to-ngx-restangular">Renaming from ng2-restangular to ngx-restangular</h1>
<p>This project was renamed from <strong>ng2-restangular</strong> to <strong>ngx-restangular</strong> due to implementation of Semantic Versioning by Angular Core Team. NPM name also changed, you can install actual version of project with <code>npm install ngx-restangular</code>.</p>
